<h2 class="dummy-h2">Focus ring</h2>

<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3">How to use</h3>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">The suggested way to apply a "focus-ring" style to an UI element is using a specific
    <strong>design token</strong>
    in your CSS code as CSS custom property:</p>
  {{! prettier-ignore-start }}
  <CodeBlock
    @language="css"
    @code="
      .your-selector {
        [...your CSS declarations]
        &:focus,
        &:focus-visible {
          box-shadow: var(--token-focus-ring-box-shadow);
        }
      }
    "
  />
  {{! prettier-ignore-end }}
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">We provide also a
    <strong>CSS helper class</strong>
    <code>.hds-focus-ring-box-shadow</code>, that is a wrapper of the design token above, but it's unlikely you can use
    it directly in a template, since this style is connected to the "focused" pseudo-state of an element (more likely it
    would be used in composition with other classes).</p>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">Which one to use will depend on the context where this style is needed and how it's applied
    (for example, could be applied using a pseudo-element).</p>

  <p class="dummy-paragraph"><strong>ðŸš¨ IMPORTANT: ðŸš¨</strong></p>
  <ul>
